        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "hornc@cray.com",
          "date": "2019-11-26 23:33:26.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-12955 lnet: Fix dest NID if sending from non-multi-rail",
        "message": "LU-12955 lnet: Fix dest NID if sending from non-multi-rail\n\nIf the originator of a message is not multi-rail capable then we\nneed to fix the destination NID of the message in order to ensure\nthat we receive a reply from a known NID. Otherwise, it is possible\nthat messages being forwarded by MR capable routers to MR capable\npeers will have a new destination NID (lnet_peer_ni) chosen by the\nrouter. Certain RPC replies will then be sent over this interface\nwhich the NMR originator may not know about. This can result in\ndropped messages.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nCray-bug-id: LUS-8102\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I5a7f0b9bc523b70a68f60598c7c19e47d30f5ccc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
